25/04/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- In a commentary published Friday (23 April), the chief of Republika Srpska's special police forces, Dragan Lukac, said police have been given until the end of April to arrest three people indicted by the UN war crimes tribunal. Lukac said High Representative Paddy Ashdown had warned that after the deadline's expiration, certain measures would be undertaken and certain individuals would be held responsible. Lukac did not elaborate. (Beta, Nezavisne Novine - 23/04/04)
